        <p>You have reached the Web space of a Narrative Medicine Project dedicated to zoonoses. Here you will find many stories told by the hands of the Professionals who have faced and treated them.  Thanks to this information, people can better defend themselves from these diseases.</p>
	<p>The Micro Epidemic One Health Project (Stories of Zoonosis) is an Experimental Zooprophylactic Institute of Umbria and Marche (e-JournalSPVet.it) initiative, setted up to give more importance to long experienced Health System Operators  and worth to seniority of service. This in order to recreate an information exchange between generations of Professionals who work to protect local communities from severe diseases such as zoonoses.</p>
	<p>The texts collected and included in the anthology "Stories of Zoonosis" are tales or interviews that account what the Doctors experienced in the course of their work. narrations communicate what they have done to fight a certain zoonotic disease; methods of intervention that others can resume or refine to use them when  in similar situations.</p>
	<p>The Micro Epidemic space is located on the Internet to welcome anyone with significant comments, observations  and additions on what has been written on the zoonoses treated.</p>
	<p>These Stories of Zoonosis are not just offered for reading, but placed in a dialoguing interface that allows interested people to expand their content, by connecting specific informational texts to open access scientific repositories, document delivery circuits, dedicated training services.</p>
	<p>Precisely because on the Net, stories become pretexts and starting points to allow peers and Citizen Scientists to sustain or complete the doctors and veterinarians reasonings by inserting their own professional experience so that the storytelling can be expanded indefinitely.</p>
